Chevron’s Deferred Income Tax Valuation Allowance rose from **$17.651 billion at the start of 2022 to $21.313 billion at year‑end 2024**, a **$3.662 billion increase**【119†L31-L38】.  The increase reflects the net effect of yearly additions versus reductions to deferred‑tax expense:  

* 2022 – Additions $3.533 bn, reductions $1.652 bn → net +$1.881 bn (balance grew to $19.532 bn)【119†L31-L36】;  
* 2023 – Additions $2.348 bn, reductions $1.464 bn → net +$0.884 bn (balance grew to $20.416 bn)【119†L31-L36】;  
* 2024 – Additions $1.881 bn, reductions $0.984 bn → net +$0.897 bn (balance grew to $21.313 bn)【119†L31-L36】.  

The cumulative net additions of $1.881 bn + $0.884 bn + $0.897 bn = **$3.662 billion**, which fully accounts for the total change in the allowance.
